summary:
I know no one really cares about Spider-Man 3 anymore, but a question recently occurred to me:
so, in the canon of the...
body:
I know no one really cares about Spider-Man 3 anymore, but a question recently occurred to me:

so, in the canon of the Raimi-movies, Peter has been pining after Mary Jane since he was six years old. right? firmly established, right? just under twenty years spent loving her by the time the third film rolls around, right? in that time, Peter has watched his chance with her slip away time and again, and even actively let it go twice. he spent a solid chunk of time knowing that she would be with him if he had not rejected her, that she had wanted him and he had said no to her so as to prioritize her safety.

and after all of that, Mary Jane still chose him. she chose him. in the third movie Peter is dating the girl of his dreams, the person he’s been loving from afar for most of his life, the person he never once thought would be his, he has her. she loves him. she left her fiance at the altar for him. so with all of this in mind…

why on GOD’S GREEN EARTH would Peter recreate a pivotal, personal moment in their relationship, their very first kiss with each other, with another person, in public, in a situation Mary Jane would absolutely be witness to in some form or other? like- I’m just- why??

summary: when they start dating, johnny notices that peter has problems with self-esteem. big problems.
body:
when they start dating, johnny notices that peter has problems with self-esteem. big problems.

it all starts with how, in response to a compliment from Johnny he only turns red and says that he is exaggerating. this is repeated next time. and in next and next too.

whenever storm has to leave for some event and he apologizes peter says he understands and that johny really needs to be there than with him. when johnny calls him with him he refuses, arguing that he does not want to embarrass him.

once, reed calls peter to the lab. Johnny knows that his boyfriend likes these scientific stuffs and comes in half an hour to check on him. to his surprise reed was truly amazed at peter’s mind, and when asked why he didn’t go to university, peter only shyly replies that he thought he wasn’t smart enough for that.

johnny tries to rectify the situation as best he can: all the time peter gives compliments (absolutely truthful ones), goes to public places with him to show that he is proud that he is his boyfriend, he throws motivational books into view, but nothing really helps. johnny almost gives up, but one case makes it clear that this is simply impossible.

peter’s self-deprecation reaches its climax in a fight with a villain.

because it is peter parker, his famous luck and stupid dedication™.

it was vulture or something like that — nothing of which the spider had previously encountered. but this time, like many others, were civilians nearby. and of course, peter prefer to hold the weight of the collapsing building on his shoulders, to give people the opportunity to leave, instead of trying to save themselves. that was all he was. it is a pity that later he was buried under the rubble and ben — ben — had to dig him out for a good ten minutes, while Johnny desperately tried to calm his heart beating in his chest.

then, in the medical wing of the baxter building, johnny, after a couple of cuddles, kisses and cuffs, asks why he simply didn’t call sue or reed, who were nearby, for help. peter says that they could get injured, and it is much easier for him to deal with them. plus their life was clearly worth more than his own.

peter says it so easily and naturally, as if he really believes in it. johnny hangs for a good couple of minutes, then dies off and firmly presses his unaware and whining to the chest his chest against the pressure.

“never dare say that your life is worth less than ours. never. you are the most amazing person I know, and if one of us is more and worthy of life, it’s you”.

peter doesn’t understand this right away, but after a while, with the help of johnny and his fantastic family, he learns to treat himself better. and johnny is just glad that his boyfriend can now love not only him, but also himself.

sorry for my mistakes but I had to share it with you

summary: today I was out books shopping and I was wearing my Midtown Tech T-Shirt which looks like this if you guys need a visual...
body:
today I was out books shopping and I was wearing my Midtown Tech T-Shirt which looks like this if you guys need a visual reference

and I was just sorta minding my own business and a guy stopped me and asked very politely where exactly the school was located. I told him it was in New York. our conversation continued and he continued to be incredibly polite, asking me if I went to school there - I told him that I didn’t. he asked me if I’d ever visited, I told him I used to live near it, which is true - I used to live in the area. he told me that he was going to research the school later (I think he was looking for magnet schools for his kids to go to). 

I……. I didn’t have the heart to tell him it was the school from Spider-Man: Homecoming.
